<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=580&amp;p=603#p603"><![CDATA[
1/2(Sun. on-line meeting only) How to Improve Your Social Life &amp;5 Ways to Make Smarter Life Decisions (Shuman))<br /><br /><br />加入 Zoom 會議<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... NKSU5MQT09<br /><br />會議 ID：929 8726 6213<br />密碼：112233<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:10-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:10 pm Break<br />8:10-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />How to Improve Your Social Life<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.wikihow.com/Improve-Your-Social-Life">http://www.wikihow.com/Improve-Your-Social-Life</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion:<br />Q1 What is your Hobbies (what would you do together?) Demeanor (serious and academic vs. humorous goof-balls, or a mix of both) Interests (similar tastes in books, movies, music, sports, etc.)Conversation habits (sit, relax and talk vs. do a lot of activities) Energy levels (raging at a bar vs. chilling at a quiet cafe)?<br />Q2 Have you ever invite your friends for dinner? Share one invitation experience which you were impressed by.<br />Q3 How frequency did you usually contact friends? Share the way how you maintain relationship.<br />Q4 In the method 2-2” Ask your current friends to bring their friends to events”, how do you think about this method? Does it work?P.S.<br /><br />Session 2: 5 Ways to Make Smarter Life Decisions<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.lifehack.org/articles/productivity/5-ways-make-smarter-life-decisions.html">https://www.lifehack.org/articles/produ ... sions.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. Identify Your Goals<br />2. Analyze the Pros and Cons<br />3. Learn from Your Mistakes<br />4. Learn from Other People’s Mistakes<br />5. Follow Your Intuition<br /><br />Discussion Questions:<br />1. Do you agree with the “5 Ways to Make Smarter Life Decisions” in the article? Any other tips?<br />2. Among the 5 tips, which one or ones do you think are more important when making smarter life decisions?<br />3. What’re the smarter or worse life decisions you have made in your life? Why?<br />4. Looking back, was there any life decision that if you hadn’t made it that way you would lead a different life or you would be a different person now?<br /><br />1.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Sun Jan 02, 2022 9:15 pm</p><hr />
